page.title: 01RESUME OF WINESTEAD
page.content:
Winestead is part of the Parish of Patrington, its boundary being just past the garage. It is a very rural area being mainly farmland and plantations. There are few houses and new building is not allowed, only extensions to existing properties.
Winestead is served by a garage, hotel and Church and also the Water Authority pumping station. There are no shops.
There is one telephone kiosk and one post box having two collections a day and one delivery. No public bus service passes through Winestead village.
